<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="515" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1726,2003]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="515" pageId="9" pageNumber="514">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1798,1823]" pageId="9" pageNumber="514">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is part of a small group of species currently placed in 
<taxonomicName box="[1086,1192,1799,1822]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eucereon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1086,1192,1799,1822]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="514">Eucereon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but that certainly do not belong in this genus. This group is here defined as comprising 
<emphasis box="[931,1297,1835,1859]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="514">
<taxonomicName box="[931,1082,1836,1859]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eucereon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maternum">E. maternum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rothschild, 1912" authorityName="Rothschild" authorityYear="1912" box="[1095,1297,1835,1859]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eucereon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscoirroratum">E. fuscoirroratum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rothschild" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" refString="Rothschild, W. (1912) New Syntomidae. Novitates Zoologicae, 19 (2), 151 - 186." type="journal article" year="1912">
Rothschild, 
<number box="[151,207,1871,1895]" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" value="1912.0">1912</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Druce, 1901" authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1901" box="[220,490,1870,1895]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eucereon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="birchelli">
<emphasis box="[220,345,1870,1895]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="514">E. birchelli</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Druce" box="[352,490,1871,1895]" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" refString="Druce, H. (1901) Descriptions of some new species of Heterocera. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 7 (7), 74 - 79. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930108678441" type="journal article" year="1901">
Druce, 
<number box="[434,490,1871,1895]" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" value="1901.0">1901</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Draudt, 1917" authorityName="Draudt" authorityYear="1917" box="[503,823,1870,1895]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eucereon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perplicatum">
<emphasis box="[503,669,1870,1895]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="514">E. perplicatum</emphasis>
Draudt, 
<number box="[767,823,1871,1895]" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" value="1917.0">1917</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Druce, 1894" authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1894" box="[837,1137,1871,1895]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eucereon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pometinum">
<emphasis box="[837,993,1871,1894]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="514">E. pometinum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Druce" box="[999,1137,1871,1895]" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" refString="Druce, H. (1894) Descriptions of some new species of Heterocera from Central America. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 6 (13), 168 - 182. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222939408677682" type="journal article" year="1894">
Druce, 
<number box="[1081,1137,1871,1895]" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" value="1894.0">1894</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rothschild, 1912" authorityName="Rothschild" authorityYear="1912" box="[1151,1429,1870,1895]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eucereon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strix">
<emphasis box="[1151,1231,1871,1894]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="514">E. strix</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rothschild" box="[1238,1429,1870,1895]" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" refString="Rothschild, W. (1912) New Syntomidae. Novitates Zoologicae, 19 (2), 151 - 186." type="journal article" year="1912">
Rothschild, 
<number box="[1373,1429,1871,1895]" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" value="1912.0">1912</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Schaus, 1896" authorityName="Schaus" authorityYear="1896" box="[151,447,1906,1931]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eucereon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="velutinum">
<emphasis box="[151,291,1906,1931]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="514">E. velutinum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schaus" box="[298,447,1906,1931]" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" refString="Schaus, W. (1896) New species of Heterocera from Tropical America. Journal of the New York Entomological Society, 4, 130 - 145." type="journal article" year="1896">
Schaus, 
<number box="[391,447,1906,1931]" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" value="1896.0">1896</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and, possibly, 
<taxonomicName authority="Schaus, 1904" authorityName="Schaus" authorityYear="1904" box="[620,916,1906,1931]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eucereon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irroratum">
<emphasis box="[620,760,1908,1931]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="514">E. irroratum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schaus" box="[766,916,1906,1931]" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" refString="Schaus, W. (1904) New species of American Heterocera. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 30, 135 - 178." type="journal article" year="1904">
Schaus, 
<number box="[860,916,1907,1931]" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" value="1904.0">1904</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Druce, 1906" authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1906" box="[929,1185,1906,1931]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eucereon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sadana">
<emphasis box="[929,1041,1906,1931]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="514">E. sadana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Druce" box="[1047,1185,1906,1931]" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" refString="Druce, H. (1906) Descriptions of some new species of Heterocera from Tropical South. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 7 (18), 77 - 94. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930608562584" type="journal article" year="1906">
Druce, 
<number box="[1129,1185,1906,1931]" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" value="1906.0">1906</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Draudt, 1917" authorityName="Draudt" authorityYear="1917" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eucereon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sarisa">
<emphasis box="[1245,1344,1908,1931]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="514">E. sarisa</emphasis>
Draudt, 
<number box="[151,207,1943,1967]" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" value="1917.0">1917</number>
</taxonomicName>
. These species most likely do not belong in 
<taxonomicName box="[720,850,1942,1967]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Ctenuchina">Ctenuchina</taxonomicName>
, but in 
<taxonomicName box="[938,1101,1942,1967]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Phaegopterina">Phaegopterina</taxonomicName>
, though the same is probably true for the core concept of 
<taxonomicName authority="Travassos 1959" authorityName="Travassos" authorityYear="1959" box="[514,837,1978,2003]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eucereon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[514,620,1980,2003]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="514">Eucereon</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Travassos" box="[643,829,1978,2003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" refString="Travassos, L. (1959) Contribuicao ao conhecimento dos Arctiidae. XLII. Genero Eucereon Huebner, 1819 (Lepidoptera, Heterocera). Memorias do Instituto Oswaldo Cruz, 57 (2), 171 - 190. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0074 - 02761959000200004" type="journal article" year="1959">
Travassos 
<number box="[772,829,1978,2003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" value="1959.0">1959</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and though 
<taxonomicName box="[1003,1163,1978,2003]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="514" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Phaegopterina">Phaegopterina</taxonomicName>
itself is probably not monophyletic (
<bibRefCitation author="Jacobson" box="[324,619,151,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515" refString="Jacobson, N. L. &amp; Weller, S. J. (2002) A cladistic study of the Arctiidae (Lepidoptera) by using characters of immatures and adults. Thomas Say Publications in Entomology: Monographs. Entomological Society of America, Lanham, 97 pp." type="book" year="2002">
Jacobson &amp; Weller 
<number box="[558,619,152,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). For all these reasons a comprehensive study must be carried out to ascertain the composition of this group, and its phylogenetic placement.
</paragraph>
